From d9f6527ca0dcb7c1dab37e137547ae93de4e79e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jarvis <jarvis@local>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 12:21:08 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Write Claude config to MSIX virtualised path for Store
 installs (#40)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Microsoft Store build of Claude Desktop is an MSIX package with
filesystem virtualisation — it reads claude_desktop_config.json from a
sandboxed container, not the real %APPDATA%\Claude\. The installer only
wrote to %APPDATA%, so MCP config silently never reached Store-installed
Claude (issue #40).

configure-claude.ps1 now discovers every Claude config location:
- Standalone: %APPDATA%\Claude\ (always configured)
- MSIX: %LOCALAPPDATA%\Packages\*Claude*\LocalCache\Roaming\Claude\
  (configured when the package's LocalCache\Roaming exists)

The per-location write/backup/verify logic is refactored into
Set-FoundryMcpConfig and applied to each target. Succeeds if at least
one location is configured; existing unrelated mcpServers and other
config keys are preserved (verified in testing).

Tested against sandboxed APPDATA/LOCALAPPDATA:
- standalone + eligible MSIX  -> both configured, existing content kept
- standalone only             -> standalone configured
- ineligible MSIX (no Roaming) -> skipped, no junk dirs created
- PowerShell parse check       -> no syntax errors

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
